<item>
            <title>[FLINK-6384] PythonStreamer does not close python processes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-6384</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;PythonStreamer&lt;/tt&gt; opens a new process calling the python binary to check whether the binary is available. This process won&apos;t get closed leading to an excessive number of open python processes when running the &lt;tt&gt;PythonPlanBinderTest&lt;/tt&gt;. I&apos;m not entirely sure whether we need this extra process, because the actual python call with the python code would also fail if there is no python binary available.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13066754">FLINK-6384</key>
            <summary>PythonStreamer does not close python processes</summary>
